cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with image dehazing and synthesis, which are primarily related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of Variational Autoencoders (VAE) and Generative Adversarial Nets (GAN) also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Maximum mean discrepancy (MMD) for training, which is a technique commonly used in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
